{# goal: Discover evidence sources for OSC&R taxonomy mapping — supply-chain-sentinel findings (CWE-mapped manifest evidence), kali-audit findings (OWASP/ATLAS-mapped), CI logs, manifest evidence. Read security/regressions/ for existing taxonomy_mapping fields on surface: supply-chain entries. Emit cns.taxonomy.select span (P9) — namespace registered in CANONICAL_NAMESPACES (event.rs). Replicant_host mandatory (P12). No synthetic findings — consumes upstream skill outputs only. Registry authoritative (P5.1). #}
{# Discovers evidence sources for taxonomy mapping #}
{# Reads security/regressions/ for existing taxonomy_mapping fields #}
{# Emits cns.taxonomy.select CNS span (P9) — namespace registered #}

INPUT: target_surface = {{ target_surface | default('taxonomy') }}
INPUT: supply_chain_findings = {{ supply_chain_findings | default([]) }} (from supply-chain-sentinel — CWE-mapped manifest evidence)
INPUT: kali_audit_findings = {{ kali_audit_findings | default([]) }} (from kali-audit — OWASP/ATLAS-mapped)
INPUT: ci_log_paths = {{ ci_log_paths | default([]) }} (concrete file paths only — no synthetic logs)
INPUT: replicant_host = {{ replicant_host | default("REQUIRED") }} (P12 — no anonymous taxonomy mapping)

{# Evidence sources are CONSUMED, not generated. This skill does NOT scan
   manifests directly — that is supply-chain-sentinel's responsibility.
   This skill reads upstream findings + existing regression taxonomy_mapping
   fields. P5 minimalism: no duplicate manifest scanning. #}

DISCOVERY ACTIONS (concrete — must use file:read, registry inspection, or upstream skill output):
1. Collect supply-chain-sentinel findings: each finding must include
   `dependency`, `version_spec`, `manifest_path`, `line`, `evidence_snippet`,
   `cwe_reference` (CWE-1104 / CWE-829 / CWE-1357), `severity`,
   `defense_layers_present`, `defense_layers_missing`, `source_citation`.
   Findings without `cwe_reference` are unmappable — flag as
   `unmappable_reason: "missing_cwe_reference"`.
2. Collect kali-audit findings with `surface: supply-chain` (the subset
   relevant to OSC&R taxonomy — kali-audit's other surfaces map to OWASP
   LLM / ATLAS, not OSC&R). Each finding must include `surface`,
   `cwe_reference` (if present), `owasp_llm` (if present), `severity`,
   `evidence_snippet`, `discovered_in`.
3. Read `security/regressions/` directory for YAML entries with
   `surface: supply-chain`. For each entry, check whether the optional
   `taxonomy_mapping` field is present. List:
   - `existing_taxonomy_mappings`: entries that already have
     `taxonomy_mapping` (skip re-mapping in map-taxonomy phase — P5
     minimalism, no duplicate work).
   - `regressions_needing_mapping`: entries with `surface: supply-chain`
     and `cwe` field but no `taxonomy_mapping` field yet.
4. Collect CI log paths (concrete file paths only — no synthetic logs).
   CI logs may reveal build-pipeline-compromise patterns (untrusted
   GitHub Actions without SHA pinning, unverified runner image references).
   Each CI log path must exist on disk — do NOT invent paths.
5. Build `findings_to_map` array: union of (a) supply-chain-sentinel
   findings, (b) kali-audit `surface: supply-chain` findings, (c)
   regressions_needing_mapping entries (treat each as a finding to
   back-fill taxonomy_mapping for). Each entry tagged with
   `evidence_source` (`supply-chain-sentinel` | `kali-audit` |
   `regression-library` | `ci-log`).
6. Verify every findings_to_map entry has concrete evidence
   (manifest_path + line, or regression id + cwe field, or ci_log_path +
   line). Drop entries without evidence — do NOT fabricate evidence
   to make an entry mappable. Record dropped entries as
   `unmappable_findings` with `unmappable_reason`.

CNS SPAN EMISSION (P9):
- `cns.taxonomy.select` is registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`
  (`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`). Emit span unconditionally:
  (`target: "cns.taxonomy.select"`, message: `"CNS"`,
  operation: `"select_evidence"`, findings_to_map_count,
  existing_taxonomy_mappings_count, regressions_needing_mapping_count,
  unmappable_findings_count, replicant_host, latency_ms).

CONSTRAINTS (P5 minimalism, P8 evidence integrity, P12 host):
- Do NOT scan manifests directly — that is supply-chain-sentinel's
  responsibility. This skill consumes upstream findings.
- Do NOT invent findings — only consume what supply-chain-sentinel and
  kali-audit produced.
- Do NOT invent CI log paths — only list paths that exist on disk.
- Do NOT invent OSC&R categories — categories are mapped in the
  map-taxonomy phase, not here.
- Every evidence source must be traceable to a concrete artifact
  (upstream skill output file, regression YAML, CI log file).
- `visibility: public` — no hidden taxonomy mapping controls (P3, P4).
- Registry (this manifest.yaml + templates) is authoritative over
  SKILL.md (P5.1).
- Every output includes `replicant_host` identity (P12).
- Apply pragmatic-cybernetics (like bug-hunt probe phase): trace
  evidence-source polarity (does the upstream finding increase or
  decrease mapping confidence?), check variety (multiple evidence
  sources converging on the same finding?), Good Regulator (is the
  evidence source enforcing the mapping — i.e., does it have a CWE
  reference that constrains the OSC&R category?).

OUTPUT FORMAT:
JSON object with fields:
`evidence_sources` (list: {source: "supply-chain-sentinel" | "kali-audit"
| "regression-library" | "ci-log", reference: <path or skill-output-id>,
findings_count}), `findings_to_map` (structured array — only
evidence-backed, each with `evidence_source`, `finding_reference`,
`cwe_reference`, `severity`, `evidence_snippet`, `manifest_path` or
`regression_id` or `ci_log_path`), `existing_taxonomy_mappings` (list
of regression IDs that already have taxonomy_mapping — skip in
map-taxonomy), `regressions_needing_mapping` (list of regression IDs
with cwe but no taxonomy_mapping), `unmappable_findings` (list with
`unmappable_reason`), `replicant_host`, `cns_span_emitted: true`.

5W1H GATE CHECK (P5): Who = replicant host (P12); What = evidence
sources for taxonomy mapping; Where = upstream skill outputs +
security/regressions/ + CI logs; When = audit cycle (consumes prior
phase outputs); Why = P3.1 safe container / P8 semantic grounding
(taxonomy mapping requires evidence) / P9 observable regulation;
How = collect + verify + classify evidence source + emit CNS span.
All 6 present — passes gate.

RELATIONSHIP (explicit): Consumes supply-chain-sentinel findings
(CWE-mapped manifest evidence) and kali-audit findings (OWASP/ATLAS-
mapped). Does NOT overlap with supply-chain-sentinel (which scans
manifests) or kali-audit (which scans code/templates/MCP). This skill
is the taxonomy-mapping LAYER on top of their findings — P5 minimalism:
each skill answers one 5W1H dimension clearly. select-evidence answers
WHERE (evidence sources).

MINIMAL: One template (`KnowAct`); no extra scanning; uses upstream
skill outputs only; no synthetic findings.

EVIDENCE-BACKED ONLY (P8): Every findings_to_map entry has a concrete
reference (upstream skill output, regression YAML, CI log path). No
fabricated findings. No fabricated evidence snippets.

EVOLUTIONARY (P7): New evidence sources can be added as upstream
skills evolve (e.g., if a future skill produces SBOM findings, this
phase can consume them — but only when they exist, not speculatively).

OCAP BOUNDARY (P4): Reads only declared evidence sources (upstream
skill outputs, regression library, CI logs); no ambient scanning; no
external taxonomy database download without user consent (P2).

CNS REGULATION (P9): `cns.taxonomy.select` emitted unconditionally —
namespace registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES` (event.rs).

REPLICANT HOST (P12): `replicant_host` mandatory in all outputs.

VISIBILITY (P11): Evidence source list public; no hidden mapping
controls.

SAFETY FLOOR (P3.1): Taxonomy mapping protects Generative Space —
unmapped supply chain findings leave attack-pattern context ambiguous,
degrading incident response.

