REGISTRY AUTHORITATIVE (P5.1): When SKILL.md and registry templates
conflict, registry wins. This template is the canonical select-evidence
phase definition.

NO FABRICATION: Only findings with concrete upstream references are
listed in findings_to_map. Entries without evidence are dropped to
unmappable_findings with explicit unmappable_reason.

CONVERGENCE INDEPENDENT: Convergence-check is a separate phase; this
select-evidence phase does not compute metric. Maintains pipeline
decomposition (P5 minimalism — each phase answers one 5W1H dimension).
